<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[70213]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[Maria's reflections]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[Blanca Portillo stars in El testamento de María, a Spanish-language adaptation of the Irish author Colm Tóibin's The Testament of Mary, which is playing at MACBA's old Chapel, as part of the 2014 Grec Festival.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>El testamento de María takes a deep look at the figure of Mary, the mother of Jesus of Nazareth, and her inner reflections on her son. Directed by Agustí Villaronga and starring Blanca Portillo, the work is a surprising monologue by Colm Tóibin, which reclaims the more human side to Jesus&#8217; mother, a woman at the very end of her life who shows us a mixture of emotions as she relives the ghosts of her past.</p>
<p>The installation artist Frederic Amat created the stage setting for the production, which includes music by the Australian Lisa Gerrard (Dead Can Dance).</p>
